    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[24 December 2020 - 5 January 2021, GoS] The data indicated that 49.2% of non-retired female respondents do not work, compared with only 21.1% of non-retired male respondents. The data also showed that 10.4% of men have more than one job, while this percentage among women does not exceed 2%. This is despite the decline in living standards in Syria, and the high percentage of the population living below the poverty line. The data collected also shows that 45.3% of female respondents stated that their reason for being unemployed was full-time housework, while none of the male respondents chose this option."/>
